.obsidian/

# Quartz (see Makefile/scripts/setup-quartz.sh, scripts/stage-content.sh) — the vendored
# engine and build output are all regenerable, not source of truth.
#
# content/ is deliberately NOT listed here even though it's also just a generated staging
# copy (scripts/stage-content.sh) — Quartz's own file walker (quartz/util/glob.ts) treats
# content/ as an Obsidian vault and respects gitignore rules to decide what to *publish*
# (its own private-notes feature), so a root-level "content/" entry here would make Quartz
# skip every staged file and silently publish an empty site. Left untracked by discipline
# instead (never `git add content`), same as japon leaves its other generated paths
# (.quartz-engine/, node_modules/, etc.) untracked without needing a rule for each.
.quartz-engine/
.quartz/
quartz/
quartz.ts
package.json
package-lock.json
tsconfig.json
globals.d.ts
index.d.ts
LICENSE.txt
.node-version
.npmrc
.prettierrc
.prettierignore
.gitattributes
node_modules/
public/
